File: platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/export-har.ts, lines 199-214.

The handler casts dispatchToExtension results with `as { requests: CapturedRequest[] }` and immediately calls `.requests.map(...)`. If the extension returns an unexpected shape (null, error object, or object without a .requests field), this crashes with 'Cannot read properties of undefined (reading map)'.

The fix is to add the same defensive validation that analyze-site/index.ts uses at lines 954-956:
```typescript
const requestsResult = await dispatchToExtension(...);
const requests = Array.isArray(requestsResult)
  ? requestsResult
  : ((requestsResult as { requests?: CapturedRequest[] }).requests ?? []);
```

Apply the same pattern to the framesResult at line 210-212.
